  <h1>
   shader_current
  </h1>
  This function will return the index ID value of the shader currently being used for rendering, or it will return -1 if no shader is being used.
  <h4>
   Syntax:
  </h4>
  <pre><code class="language-gml">shader_current();
</code></pre>
  <h4>
   Returns:
  </h4>
  <pre><code class="language-gml"><a href="../../../../../The_Asset_Editors/Shaders.htm">
 Shader Asset
</a>
or -1 (if no shader is assigned)
</code></pre>
  <h4>
   Example:
  </h4>
  <pre><code class="language-gml">if (shader_current() == -1)
{
    shader_set(sh_warp)
}
</code></pre>
  The above code will check to see what the current shader is and if it returns -1 (no shader being used) then a shader is set.
 </body>
</html>